{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add focused prerequisite consistency review\n\n## Goal\nEvaluate whether a ticket plan remains consistent with each direct prerequisite without injecting prerequisite material into general reviewers or changing existing parent and child review behavior.\n\n## Upstream contract\nThis story implements against the certified material-pin interface from `75de-02b0-d454-410b` and review-phase interface from `5967-4476-7f9f-442d`. The pin interface supplies one review-time `PlanRelationSnapshot` preload keyed by authoritative canonical ticket ID, including relation kind, readable state, pinned material, and ticket plan text. This story neither recollects relations nor changes parent and child context handling.\n\n## Implementation\n- Register one prerequisite-consistency criterion. It runs only when the shared `PlanRelationSnapshot` preload succeeded and contains readable direct `depends_on` or inverse `blocks` prerequisites. The same canonical ID reached through both relation forms is evaluated once.\n- Add named prompt constants `PASS_PREREQUISITE_FINDER = \"plan-review-prerequisite-finder\"` and `PASS_PREREQUISITE_VERIFIER = \"plan-review-prerequisite-verifier\"` in `passes.py`. Extend the production Pass-1 batch runner with the prerequisite-only finder route. It receives the subject plan plus stable-order whole prerequisite blocks, packs as many blocks as fit, and invokes `plan_review_prerequisite_coverage`. General criterion requests retain their existing inputs.\n- Define measurable isolation: capture every request and assert that each general finder, general verifier, and coach system prompt, user prompt, and instructions contain neither prerequisite canonical IDs nor prerequisite plan text. Assert exactly one relation preload supplies both pin creation and prerequisite routing. Only the two focused prerequisite prompts may receive prerequisite material.\n- Define `_prerequisite_coverage_model()` in `passes.py` with outer `PrerequisiteCoverageOutput { records: list[PrerequisiteCoverageRecord] }`. Each record is `{prerequisite_id: canonical string, disposition: consistent|finding|indeterminate, findings: list[Finding], reason_code?: evaluation-error|output-invalid|attribution-invalid, detail?: string}`. Add `contracts.register_contract(\"plan_review_prerequisite_coverage\", _prerequisite_coverage_model)` to the existing `passes.register_contracts()` function.\n- Require exactly one record per readable pinned canonical ID. `consistent` requires no findings or reason code. `finding` requires at least one finding and no reason code, with every finding carrying that canonical `prerequisite_id`. `indeterminate` requires no findings and one closed-enum reason code. Missing, duplicate, unknown-ID, parse-invalid, or schema-invalid output maps unresolved IDs in the bin to `output-invalid`. Provider failure maps them to `evaluation-error`. Indeterminate records never assert incompatibility.\n- Keep batching semantically neutral. Every focused Pass-1 prompt asks for independent subject-to-one-prerequisite judgments and forbids cross-prerequisite findings. Stable bins contain whole blocks only. Neither the subject nor a prerequisite is split. A conflict in the last stable-order block is evaluated identically to a singleton call.\n- Use the parent-approved existing index-keyed `plan_review_verification` schema for focused Pass 2 rather than adding another verification contract. Extend its shared `Binary` with optional `prerequisite_attribution_valid=yes|no|na`; default absent values to `na`, include it in `_BINARY_NA_DEFAULT`, and exclude it from `GRADED_BINARY`, making it a veto rather than a validity contributor. General findings use `na` and preserve existing validity math.\n- The focused verifier receives the subject plan and, for each local finding, the authoritative prerequisite ID and plan block from the preload. It emits the existing `{index, severity_attributes, binary}` entry. Set `prerequisite_attribution_valid=yes` only when the indexed finding is supported by that exact subject-prerequisite pair; set `no` for wrong or unprovable attribution. `na` is valid only for non-prerequisite findings. Multiple whole focused records may share a call within the context budget.\n- Preserve two non-overlapping index domains through verification. General `findings[]` and `verifications[]` retain their current global domain `0..G-1`. Flatten focused findings separately in stable `(prerequisite_id, finding_index)` order into local domain `0..P-1`, and run the focused verifier against only that list. Never inject focused findings into the general arrays.\n- In `plan_review_decide`, independently reshape and decide each domain. Run the existing general path unchanged. For the focused domain, missing, duplicate, malformed, out-of-range, `no`, or `na` attribution converts that prerequisite record to `indeterminate/attribution-invalid` and removes its incompatibility findings. Run `pass3_over_findings` on remaining focused findings with focused verifications and the phase story threshold function. Concatenate `general_decided + focused_decided` only after both calls return, then invoke the existing single `partition_findings` call with DET findings. Thus upheld focused findings surface normally in blocking or advisory arrays with their canonical `prerequisite_id`, without shifting any general index.\n- Size the actual focused prompt topology, including system prompt, subject plan, prerequisite or finding blocks, output reserve, and headroom, through a prerequisite-specific adapter in `sizing.py`. On a context-limit error, split a stable bin into contiguous halves recursively. Escalate a singleton through `models_at_or_above()`. Largest-window exhaustion emits `indeterminate/evaluation-error` with `detail=input-too-large`. Non-context provider failure emits `indeterminate/evaluation-error` for every unresolved ID.\n- Add optional `has_prerequisites`, `prerequisite_coverage`, `prerequisite_findings`, and `prerequisite_verifications` properties to `plan_review_decide_input.schema.json`; do not use conditional JSON Schema requirements. Both YAML branches always pass the fields, using false and empty arrays when the route does not apply. Python-level validation inside `plan_review_decide` requires complete arrays when `has_prerequisites=true`. Extend decide output and coach input schemas with final coverage records.\n- Wire focused finder and verifier steps and all focused arrays through both agentic and single-turn branches in `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml`. Thread final coverage into `plan_review_coach`, which sets `coverage.prerequisite_indeterminate=true` when any record is indeterminate. Per the epic contract, `orchestrator.finalize_verdict` tests this flag before existing verdict branches and forces top-level `INDETERMINATE`; the existing signing boundary signs only PASS, so it remains unsigned and uncertifiable.\n- Add optional `gold_prerequisite_id` and `pred_prerequisite_id` fields to `parity.ItemRecord`, both defaulting to `None`. Preserve existing fields, `CONTAINER_CRITERIA`, `attribution_accuracy`, `packing_spot_eval`, and `container_fidelity_report` behavior. Add `prerequisite_fidelity_report` for authoritative-ID attribution plus existing recall and false-acceptance calculations. Existing container gold-corpus results remain unchanged.\n- Add separate opt-in `prerequisite_packing_spot_eval`; do not route prerequisite data through `packing_spot_eval` or `container_fidelity_report`. Add at least eight gold sets of at least three prerequisites: two all-consistent, two single-conflict, two tail-conflict with the conflict last in stable order, one attribution-confusion, and one multi-bin case. Compare packed with singleton calls. Packed recall may not decrease, false acceptance may not increase, every readable ID must have one record, and attribution errors must be zero. Failure retains smaller bins or singleton calls.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] General finder, general verifier, and coach requests contain no prerequisite IDs or plan text.\n- [ ] One relation preload supplies both material-pin creation and prerequisite routing.\n- [ ] Existing parent and child criteria retain their existing container gold-corpus results.\n- [ ] Stable focused batching never splits the subject or a prerequisite block.\n- [ ] Every readable pinned prerequisite receives exactly one closed-schema coverage disposition.\n- [ ] Focused verification uses the existing registered index-keyed Pass-2 contract with the optional `yes|no|na` attribution field.\n- [ ] General and focused verification index domains are independently reshaped and cannot shift each other.\n- [ ] Missing or incorrect canonical attribution cannot produce a blocking finding.\n- [ ] Every upheld focused finding appears in the verdict partition with its verified authoritative prerequisite ID.\n- [ ] Every indeterminate record contains no incompatibility finding.\n- [ ] Any indeterminate prerequisite record forces top-level unsigned INDETERMINATE.\n- [ ] Largest-window exhaustion emits `indeterminate/evaluation-error` with `detail=input-too-large` before top-level remediation.\n- [ ] The separate opt-in prerequisite evaluation meets recall, false-acceptance, coverage, and attribution thresholds.\n\n## Verification\n- Run `.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/unit/test_plan_review.py tests/unit/test_plan_review_prerequisites.py tests/unit/workflow/test_plan_review_workflow.py`.\n- Run `.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/interfaces/contracts/test_plan_review_prerequisite_isolation.py tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_review_gate.py`.\n- Run the new opt-in prerequisite packing evaluation and record its result in a ticket comment.\n- Run `make check` and `.venv/bin/python -m pytest -m \"not integration\"`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784562936380759001,"uuid":"47a7e5aa-c810-4203-867d-f3485e2019bf"}